ly; in either case we will earn our fate, good or bad: it will not be imposed issue from our own Acts. on us but will This is a whole new spiritual, theological the Bible eschatological view not found in (it is, however, compatable with Zoroaster‐ This is clearly the greatest choice lanism!) that we as a species have ever faced, to choose rightly is to live + to live in total spiritual union with Christ, to choose wrongly is physically to die; there is no middle ground. + it is all literal + real actual + concerns this world. By virtue + of Christ's penetration of the ecosphere, the next world is brought here, + yet we can lose it by our choice we totally determine the future one way -direction - or the other (its opposite). will now be possible to see Christ in t if C-54 + as every living creature - not just humans - +, finally, in + as the totality of the ecosphere itself as an indivisible sentient, conscious, biological unity evolving + becoming more + more structured (negen‐ tropic) This all can be looked at two ways. 1) contemporary concern about preserving the ecosphere is supplied with a spiritual dimension that is both cosmic + absolute. specifically 2) Religion + the spiritual - + Xtianity with its eschatological doctrines - is brought down to earth -literally - + tied into realistic, practical matters. This is an amazing fusion, resulting in a vast new overview never before glimpsed - in particular, the realization (idea) that we as a species have the power of choice as to whether on the one hand our ecosphere will remain divinized. [Note] or, on the other hands we will by our own actions drive this spiritual + life-giving power away + thus doom ourselves to physical extinction. ➀ + we ourselves divinized by our participation in it Thus there emerges from this a doctrine of the final judgment being more correctly a final choice on our parts between life - spiritual life, a higher life - + death, physical death. C-56 uream: on a bank of to screens, scenes of a hunt in progress; the victim is a lovely large white bird. I become very angry at the hunt itself + at all the people watching in/as a video game/sport. I lash out at them, saying I won't watch, + I say, \"Maybe Caesar will put in an appearance. This dream clearly ties in Tagore's Kerygma (about saving the animals) with Rome + hence with the Empire + hence with early Xtianity. Now not humans are the victims of the sports for the populace but animals, but blood it is the same cruelty. Sh - \"Caesar\" was said sardonically, in reference to reagan! good Lord! Look, then, what the dream shows, at least about my feelings/perception! about who is the enemy, + who we are. Xtianity in i its time sanctified human life ( the opposite of which was the Roman games) but now all life - animal life - the ecosphere itself must be sanctified, + this is done through its investiture by Christ. To \"see\" (understand) the ecosphere as having been penetrated + Holy; assimilated by Christ is to see it as Thus this 3rd dispensation is indeed the logical extension projected from the previous two could reason that my vision of Thus I Valis in/as nature (in 3-74) was to prepare me for the spiritual comprehension of Tagore's Kerygma; I did not think at the time - not until the 9-81 vision - that \"world\" or \"reality really meant \"ecosphere\"; this has come as a complete surprise to me; a revelation indeed, Christ is a revolutionary. The ultimate revo lutionary. + he has magical (technological?) powers. + he is still alive. This explains it all, from \"Tears\" thru 2-3-74 to Tagore t s C-57 against the Empire. What is it really religious? Hat: \"PKD,, PKD\" + this is 2-3-74; PKD, surfaced. + this is Ditheon. there is literally a masterminis guiding this + it is revolution hypnagogic: I mad out the 85 \"notices\" - the mmothon runners ED Mesky, Xerox image: carring the Torch: two of them, picking up the Torah + running in different directions; there are at least i.e. out of the 85 people